    {
      "id": "PopularPost315341",
      "post_content": "Yeah, this guy looks solid, but he really, really isn't. If you are on the draw, this gives your opponent twelve mana to play with. I have never seen this guy live a turn in Limited, but I have seen him power out a massive pile of fatties on the other side of the board and provide the fuel for an unrecoverable Revelation (draw 9, gain 9 life, nuke the board with Verdict next turn after opponent plays out their hand). Maybe the way to play him is to wait until turn seven, leaving up a counterspell so that your opponent needs two answers to the beast, but his upside has been all downside so far. A card for the casual crowd, and only those who enjoy losing in epic fashion.",
      "posted_by": "CapmCrunch",
